From David Ward Subject Re HST Servicing Mission Scheduled for Days In article Bruce Scott If re boosting the HST by carrying it with a shuttle would not damage it then why couldn't HST be brought back to earth and the repair job done here Is it because two shuttle flights would be required adding to the alredy horrendous expense I don't think a reboost exercise is analogous to a shuttle landing launch in terms of stresses misalignments I would think of the reboost as a gentile push where a landing then launch as two JOLTS which would put more mechanical stress on the Additionally there might be a concern about landing loads to the shuttle in the event of a laden Finally probably some thought went into possible contamination problems if the instruments came back to Of course the cost of two shuttle launches is a good reason to avoid something that might be done in one shuttle Here's hoping Cepi's gang gets the job done right the first David GSFC I used to work for Frank Cepollina